      ## Retro

      **What went well:** Race reproduced deterministically (writeDelayMs=2500 + lingerMs=100 vs the watcher's 5s pollIntervalMs) before any code change, then ran 10x under load to confirm the fix is stable. Quality gates flagged a real defensive gap (drain rejection would strand the job inside an async Node 'close' listener) and that fix shipped in the same commit. Single Fork Principle preserved — no second spawn, no second observer; just one extra `drain()` call on the existing watcher.

      **What went wrong:** First fix iteration introduced 24 unit-test failures because the close handler signature changed sync → async. Each test had to await a microtask after `child.emit("close", N)`. The mock-watcher call-order assertion in launcher.test.ts also needed an update (drain runs once in close handler + once in cleanup; both are needed for different invariants — summary capture and dispatchTracker totals). Caught and fixed before commit.

      **Action items:** Nothing
      **Commits:** 9bf2e50
